						<summary>

						<p>A fragment built into the wall of the Kāśiviśvanāthasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">[Parakēsarivarmaṉ Rājēndradēva] (II) No date: c. 11th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription forms part of a long record of the king a part of whose <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> is preserved here.</p>						

						<p>It refers to an image of the god Karumāṇikka ••• ••• in standing posture, in the Vishṇu temple called [••••] ṇagar-Āḻvār temple. Mentions a certain Śirunaṁgaichchāṉi, a Brāhmaṇi.</p>						

						</summary>
